reviews.review: As a finale to episodes 7 and 8 it was amazing. if you like movies because they are movies then you will like it. if you are a fan that was disappointed and annoyed after episode 8 this film is a redeemer. if you are a pre Disney fanatic for Star Wars then stay home. I enjoyed my two and a half hour romp across a galaxy far, far away and if you go, I hope you do too.

Burdo intento de recuperar las ideas del Ep. VII pero sin conseguirlo. Esta película nos muestra una gran discontinuidad con la anterior de la saga, los cambios de dirección no han ayudado nada. Errores "enmendados", nuevos poderes de la fuerza que se sienten como un Deus Ex Machina tras otro, ideas recicladas de la Trilogía Original... Un desastre de principio a fin que además se siente demasiado frenético durante todo el film, especialmente la primera hora. Quieren contar demasiado y no les da tiempo.

I don't know why everyone is hating on it so much. I thought it was a fun watch. Nothing will ever compare to the original trilogy but it was much better than 1-3. I loved seeing this movie and low-key had tears in my eyes through at least half of it.

Good action but like anything that JJ Abrams directs that story was rushed, that characters and their relationships where not developed and end the end everything was muddied.  Abrams is a poor story teller!
A Star Wars fan since 1977. Great to see it come to fruition. The boyfriend slept through it but he as not a fan like me. Good movie if you are a fan otherwise maybe not...

I think it was an adventure and I enjoyed the banter between the various characters. I wish the movie was an hour longer just because we were hit with so much to process. But overall, solid and it definitely helps if you watch the other two prequels beforehand. There’s lots of little details that you might not catch unless you do. Currently buying a ticket to watch it a third time. Go watch it, you’ll have fun.
I'm no Star Wars buff but I love Star Wars and I loooooooooooved this movie!
Always loved the franchise and they did a good job closing loose ends. Action packed from start to end.
Like the concepts, but felt rushed.
